parameters: (From the rushing water pops out large lizards.)
\n<Sabrina>I dunno but they sure are ugly.
(A ball gets thrown by an unknown source. The lizards all smell it then it.)
(This causes lizards to screech then stumble and dive back into the river.)
\n<FEDERICK>You two look out of your element!
\n<FEDERICK>Yes! Well then, that makes introductions easier.
\n<FEDERICK>Tell me, was it my research papers, my books, or my theory on safe chaos
energy. I think I might need to redo some calculations-
\n<Adam>Mm-hmm, we know your son. Im ADAM and this is SABRINA.
\n<FEDERICK>I knew it, the only one who could find me would be my little CHARLES.
(FEDERICK does a little dance. SABRINA snickers at this.)
\n<Sabrina>I didnt know his dad was this goofy.
\n<Adam>Uh, Mr. MCHUBBLE, where are we exactly?
(FEDERICK stops dancing and has a blank expression.)
(He hands the two glowing subway pass cards.)
\n<Adam>Yeah, dont you need one as well?
\n<FEDERICK>Unfortunately, I am unable to use them.
\n<FEDERICK>Fret not, I know this place holds the means of my escape!
(He pulls out an old notebook and flips through the pages.)
\n<FEDERICK>You see, I am not sure where we are exactly but my theory is thatthis is some
\n<Adam>What made you come to that conclusion?
\n<FEDERICK>Because I knew this was a possibility. I caused this.
\n<FEDERICK>But, dont tell CHARLES- I know thinks highly of me.
\n<Adam>But, we will help you find a way out.
\n<Sabrina>Thats right, you can count on us!
\n<FEDERICK>No, I couldnt. You two have already risked your lives getting here, I could
\n<FEDERICK>Knowing my CHARLES is in good hands is enough for me.
\n<FEDERICK>Balderdash, Ive been doing well on my own so far!
\n<FEDERICK>Not in this place. Do not take it lightly. Even for some rookie Knights.
\n<Adam>Well do anything to prove we can handle it.
\n<Adam>No, but lets just hear him out.
\n<FEDERICK>I need you to get the skull of a water slime.
\n<FEDERICK>Whats the matter? You did say any task?
\n<Sabrina>Nah, we can totally do it but it gonna be a pain in the ass. Fire and Water
\n<FEDERICK>That is about it, be aware of your surroundings - danger lurks aroundevery
(FEDERICK begins unpacking the stuff he is carrying.)
\n<FEDERICK>If you need help or find anything interesting bring it back to me. I might be
able put them to good use.
